# Social Analytics — API Parameters & Database Schema

## Platform-by-Platform API Breakdown

---

### 1. 📸 Instagram (Meta Graph API)

**Endpoint (per post):** `GET /{ig-media-id}/insights`  
**Endpoint (account-level):** `GET /{ig-user-id}/insights`  
**Auth Required:** `instagram_basic`, `instagram_manage_insights` permissions  
**Account Requirement:** Must be a Business or Creator account linked to a Facebook Page  

> [!IMPORTANT]
> As of **April 21, 2025 (v22.0+)**, `impressions` and `plays` are **deprecated**. The new primary metric is `media_views`.

| API Field | Maps To Our Column | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `media_views` | `impressions` | Replaces old `impressions` metric |
| `reach` | `reach` | Unique accounts that saw the post |
| `likes` | `likes` | Total likes |
| `comments` | `comments` | Total comments |
| `shares` | `shares` | Times shared |
| `saved` | `saves` | Times saved to collection |
| `engagement` | computed | Total interactions (sum) |
| `reels_skip_rate` | `skip_rate` | Reels only — % skipped in 3s |
| `profile_visits` | `profile_visits` | Profile visits from post |
| `follows` | `new_followers` | New follows from post |

**Credentials Needed:**
- `INSTAGRAM_USER_ACCESS_TOKEN` (long-lived, 60-day, refreshable)
- `INSTAGRAM_BUSINESS_ACCOUNT_ID`
- `FACEBOOK_APP_ID` + `FACEBOOK_APP_SECRET`

---

### 2. 💼 LinkedIn (Marketing API)

**Endpoint (page stats):** `GET /rest/organizationPageStatistics`  
**Endpoint (post/share stats):** `GET /rest/organizationalEntityShareStatistics`  
**Auth Required:** OAuth 2.0, `r_organization_social_admin` permission  
**Granularity:** `DAY` or `MONTH` with epoch timestamps  

| API Field | Maps To Our Column | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `allPageViews.pageViews` | `impressions` | Total page views |
| `overviewPageViews.uniquePageViews` | `reach` | Unique page views |
| `totalClicks` | `clicks` | CTA + link clicks |
| `likes` (share stats) | `likes` | Reactions on posts |
| `comments` | `comments` | Comments on posts |
| `shares` | `shares` | Reshares |
| `engagement` (calculated) | `engagement_rate` | (clicks+likes+comments+shares)/impressions |
| `followers` | `followers` | Follower count at snapshot |

**Credentials Needed:**
- `LINKEDIN_ACCESS_TOKEN` (OAuth 2.0)
- `LINKEDIN_ORGANIZATION_URN` (e.g. `urn:li:organization:12345678`)

---

### 3. 🌐 Website / Blog (Google Analytics 4)

**Endpoint:** `POST https://analyticsdata.googleapis.com/v1beta/properties/{propertyId}:runReport`  
**Auth Required:** Service Account JSON key  
**Dimensions:** `date`, `pagePath`, `deviceCategory`  

| GA4 Metric | Maps To Our Column | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `screenPageViews` | `impressions` | Total page views |
| `activeUsers` | `reach` | Unique visitors |
| `sessions` | `sessions` | Total sessions |
| `bounceRate` | `bounce_rate` | % single-page sessions |
| `averageSessionDuration` | `avg_time_on_page` | Seconds |
| `conversions` | `conversions` | Goal completions |
| `newUsers` | `new_visitors` | First-time visitors |

**Credentials Needed:**
- `GA4_PROPERTY_ID` (e.g. `properties/123456789`)
- `GOOGLE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_JSON` (service account key file)

---

## ✅ Final `social_analytics` Table SQL

Run this in **Supabase → SQL Editor**:

```sql
-- Drop and recreate with full schema
create table if not exists social_analytics (
  id                uuid default gen_random_uuid() primary key,
  
  -- Link to post (optional — account-level rows have no post_id)
  post_id           uuid references content_deliverables(id) on delete set null,
  client_id         uuid references clients(id) on delete cascade,
  
  -- Platform identifier
  platform          text not null check (platform in ('instagram', 'linkedin', 'website')),
  
  -- ── Shared metrics (all platforms) ──
  impressions       integer default 0,   -- media_views (IG), allPageViews (LI), screenPageViews (GA4)
  reach             integer default 0,   -- reach (IG), uniquePageViews (LI), activeUsers (GA4)
  likes             integer default 0,   -- likes / reactions
  comments          integer default 0,   -- comments
  shares            integer default 0,   -- shares / reshares
  engagement_rate   numeric(6,2) default 0,  -- % engagement

  -- ── Instagram-specific ──
  saves             integer default 0,   -- saved to collection
  profile_visits    integer default 0,   -- profile visits from post
  new_followers     integer default 0,   -- follows gained
  skip_rate         numeric(5,2) default 0, -- reels skip rate %
  
  -- ── LinkedIn-specific ──
  clicks            integer default 0,   -- link + CTA clicks
  followers         integer default 0,   -- follower count snapshot

  -- ── Website-specific ──
  sessions          integer default 0,   -- GA4 sessions
  bounce_rate       numeric(5,2) default 0, -- bounce %
  avg_time_on_page  integer default 0,   -- seconds
  conversions       integer default 0,   -- goal completions
  new_visitors      integer default 0,   -- first-time users

  -- ── Meta / audit ──
  data_source       text default 'manual',  -- 'meta_api' | 'linkedin_api' | 'ga4_api' | 'manual'
  recorded_at       timestamp with time zone default now(),
  created_at        timestamp with time zone default now()
);

-- RLS
alter table social_analytics enable row level security;
create policy "Allow all" on social_analytics for all using (true) with check (true);

-- Index for fast date-range queries
create index if not exists idx_social_analytics_recorded_at on social_analytics(recorded_at desc);
create index if not exists idx_social_analytics_platform    on social_analytics(platform);
create index if not exists idx_social_analytics_client      on social_analytics(client_id);

-- Seed data with all columns populated
insert into social_analytics 
  (platform, impressions, reach, likes, comments, shares, saves, engagement_rate, recorded_at, data_source)
values
  ('instagram', 4200, 3800, 312, 45, 28, 91, 7.42, now() - interval '6 days', 'meta_api'),
  ('linkedin',  2100, 1900, 180, 32, 15, 0,  8.57, now() - interval '5 days', 'linkedin_api'),
  ('instagram', 5600, 4900, 428, 67, 41, 138, 7.64, now() - interval '4 days', 'meta_api'),
  ('website',   1800, 1600,  0,  12,  0, 0,  5.00, now() - interval '3 days', 'ga4_api'),
  ('instagram', 6300, 5700, 510, 88, 52, 164, 8.09, now() - interval '2 days', 'meta_api'),
  ('linkedin',  3100, 2800, 240, 41, 22, 0,  7.74, now() - interval '1 day',  'linkedin_api'),
  ('instagram', 7200, 6400, 620, 102, 65, 201, 8.61, now(),                   'meta_api');
```

